  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are in a geopolitical risk-on/risk-off cycle with US-Iran tensions creating oil volatility while hopes for diplomatic resolution drive late-session rallies. The bear market relief rally remains intact as oil pulls back from highs, 10Y yields fall to 4.3%, and equities recover despite forward P/E compression.",
    "regimeImpact": "The oversold relief rally assessment remains valid as oil retreated from stagflation thresholds, yields stayed below 4.50% growth stress levels, and late-session equity rallies show resilient risk appetite despite geopolitical noise.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR ladder closely as Bitcoin bounced to $72.5K, approaching potential resistance levels for put strike management",
      "Prepare to reduce short book size if SPY can reclaim and hold above 662 (200 SMA) on sustained diplomatic progress",
      "Maintain Maturity sector overweight as defensive positioning during ongoing geopolitical uncertainty and potential oil volatility"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil pullback from highs removes immediate stagflation risk while 10Y yield drop to 4.3% relieves growth stress concerns.",
      "Bitcoin's bounce to $72.5K tests key resistance while wallet activity remains at 2019 lows, suggesting limited institutional participation.",
      "Fed's Goolsbee warned of consumer confidence souring from higher gasoline prices if Iran conflict extends beyond short-term.",
      "Forward P/E compression to lowest since 'Liberation Day' selloff indicates earnings season will be critical for sustained rally continuation."
